{"in": {"title": "Questing Lores", "subtitle": "<span id=\"tr_lore_id\">a blank slate is the best slate</span>", "lines": ["NARRATOR: How to perform an AVL Tree Rotation in the most melodramatic way possible.", "SCENE: https://www.soundjay.com/misc/dream-harp-06.mp3 (no wait)", "NARRATOR: Welcome to BinaryLand! Here in BinaryLand, there are no shades of grey. There's only a series of extremes. Either people love each other to the bitter end, or they can't stand each other.", "SCENE:&nbsp;https://www.soundjay.com/human/crowd-talking-3.mp3 (no wait)", "NARRATOR: Let's look at how two different families go through a period of great imbalance!", "FIRST CHILD: (x-loud) I hate you!&nbsp; I wish I was adopted!", "FIRST PARENT: (x-loud) All I did was tell you that everyone these days speaks Python!", "FIRST CHILD: (x-loud) I don't want to speak Python!&nbsp; You're terrible!&nbsp; I hate you!&nbsp; I have two kids of my own now and I'm going to make sure neither of them ever learn one word of Python.", "FIRST PARENT: I can't believe you're related to me.", "FIRST GRANDPARENT: (sighs) Okay, fine, I'll move in across the street from the FirstParent and speak C++ to them.&nbsp; Maybe that'll calm things down.", "NARRATOR: Our FirstFamily has a bit of a difficult relationship between the parent and the child.&nbsp; You could say that they have... binary opposite personalities.&nbsp; In fact, if this were a binary tree, you could even say that (parent &amp; 1) ^ 1 == (child &amp; 1).", "FIRST PARENT: Narrator, what the heck are you even talking about?", "FIRST GRANDPARENT: You skipped your binary operators lesson, didn't you?", "FIRST PARENT: It's just so easy to skip it in Python!", "FIRST CHILD: I'm gonna make sure my kids grow up only speaking Rust!", "FIRST PARENT: (x-loud) You'll speak Rust over my dead body!", "FIRST GRANDPARENT: (sighs) I bet you $10 they'll grow up speaking only Java.", "SCENE:&nbsp;https://www.soundjay.com/misc/magic-chime-07.mp3 (no wait)", "NARRATOR: Anyways let's look at another family. In SecondFamily, the parent and child are on friendlier terms. The dynamics are a little different.", "SECOND PARENT: I'm so glad we are so close.&nbsp; I'd take a bullet for you.", "SECOND CHILD: That's great to hear, because I'm about to get arrested.", "SECOND PARENT: (x-loud) Wait, what?!", "SECOND CHILD: But since we get along so well together, you know, what with both of us being on the same side and all, why don't I just move into your house and pretend to be you?", "SECOND PARENT: (soft) Well I guess that's okay but you're kind of putting me in the hot-seat over here.", "SECOND CHILD: No, I'm putting you at the root!", "SECOND PARENT: I guess we should get grandpa to move across the street from my old house.", "SECOND GRANDPARENT: (calling) Already doing it!", "NARRATOR: As SecondChild has just pointed out, in both families, the child is in hot water. Serious hot water. In fact, they're about to be put into the hot seat which some non-BinaryLand residents may refer to as the root.", "SCENE:&nbsp;https://www.soundjay.com/free-music/barn-beat-01.mp3 (no wait)", "FIRST CHILD: You're my parent!&nbsp; You're supposed to protect me from going to the root!", "FIRST PARENT: You said you were learning Rust.&nbsp; So you can go to the root and rot there as far as I'm concerned.", "NARRATOR: Meanwhile, in SecondFamily...", "SCENE:&nbsp;https://www.soundjay.com/free-music/destination-01.mp3 (no wait)", "SECOND PARENT: (sobs) It was me, officer.&nbsp; I did it, not my child.&nbsp; Send me to the root instead!&nbsp; You can see that my child is such a good kid, they've already moved into my old location in the tree.", "OFFICER: Oh, yes, I can see that.&nbsp; And grandpa has moved in across the street.", "SECOND GRANDPARENT: Well, clearly.&nbsp; The grandparent always moves across the street from the parent's old location.", "FIRST GRANDPARENT: Yeah, that always happens.&nbsp; No matter what the circumstances.&nbsp; It's just always true.", "SECOND GRANDPARENT: You can't claim to be an AVL tree balancer without knowing that the grandpa's new location is always parent's old location ^ 1.&nbsp; It's like AVL tree balancing 101.", "NARRATOR: Why is that?", "SHOSHI: Oh, I've got a whole presentation and a paper explaining...!", "NARRATOR: Forget it, I don't want to know.&nbsp; Let's just get back to our family drama, okay?", "OFFICER: Well, SecondParent, since you're going to take the blame, I guess that means you're moving into the hot-seat, huh?", "SECOND PARENT: I'm prepared to go to the root if I must.&nbsp; Anything so SecondChild doesn't have to be separated from his/her kids.", "NARRATOR: Meanwhile, things are not nearly so quiet over at FirstFamily.", "OFFICER: FirstChild, you are officially in the hot seat.&nbsp; It's time for you to be moved to the root.&nbsp; Your children will be taken from you and placed in a more deserving, more loving household.", "FIRST CHILD: No!&nbsp; Not my children!&nbsp; (sobs)", "FIRST GRANDPARENT: It's okay.&nbsp; I will adopt one and teach them the ways of C++.", "FIRST CHILD: Which one?", "FIRST GRANDPARENT: The one you don't like.&nbsp; You know.&nbsp; The one with the opposite personality to you.", "FIRST CHILD: What?!&nbsp; But what will happen to my other child?!", "FIRST PARENT: That child is going to take your old spot in the tree -- directly under me!&nbsp; How do you like that?", "FIRST CHILD: Nooooooo!!!!", "FIRST PARENT: Whatever.&nbsp; I'm not moving.", "NARRATOR: And so our drama ends.&nbsp; Although there has been a period of great imbalance, we have now overcome it by moving everyone around and bringing the tree of our neighborhood into balance.&nbsp; I hope you all learned something.&nbsp; I, for one, learned that the grandparent always moves across the street from the parent.", "AVL TREE INVENTOR: (turning off TV) Shoshi, this is not what I had in mind when I said \"left-left\" and \"right-right\" and \"left-right\" and \"right-left\".", "SHOSHI: Yes, I know, but this way is better for dyslexic people.", "AVL TREE INVENTOR: Shoshi, you are a very strange person.", "SHOSHI: That's fair."], "speaker_map": {"NARRATOR": "Joanna", "&nbsp;https": "Joanna", "SCENE": "Joanna", "FIRSTCHILD(x-loud)": "Joanna", "FIRSTPARENT(x-loud)": "Joanna", "FIRSTPARENT": "Joanna", "FIRSTGRANDPARENT(sighing)": "Joanna", "FIRSTGRANDPARENT": "Joanna", "FIRSTCHILD": "Joanna", "FIRST CHILD": "Kimberly", "FIRST PARENT": "Joey", "FIRST GRANDPARENT": "Justin", "SECOND PARENT": "Amy", "SECOND CHILD": "Emma", "SECOND GRANDPARENT": "Brian", "OFFICER": "Geraint", "SHOSHI": "Salli", "AVL TREE INVENTOR": "Matthew"}}, "out": {"cache_id": "5cfca4bcd17f081918ab6add81933d42", "audio_objects": [["6daaa8f096c421af0305ae1b0b9162d2-how-to-perform-an-avl-tre---", 0], ["https://www.soundjay.com/misc/dream-harp-06.mp3", 1], ["d267eb71f93900982c55e3141532aef2-welcome-to-binaryland--he---", 0], ["https://www.soundjay.com/human/crowd-talking-3.mp3", 1], ["44c9cb6293f336ff01095f5f19c38922-let-s-look-at-how-two-dif---", 0], ["51502218d5fb2d1b6c132907ee4fef07--i-hate-you---i-wish-i-wa---", 0], ["92e99d5f29d6cada9b79a54cba80e340--all-i-did-was-tell-you-t---", 0], ["5a175e01fe8b1f131d2732a2eb8d7d37--i-don-t-want-to-speak-py---", 0], ["53eca6949a4bacf7c36fb65226d3d41e-i-can-t-believe-you-re-re---", 0], ["a10c7797580ab93ab12335024b38e302--okay--fine--i-ll-move-in---", 0], ["8ca126b1b1b96d94a9636087ba366298-our-firstfamily-has-a-bit---", 0], ["d88572903e4bdace6c2a670485ce1526-narrator--what-the-heck-a---", 0], ["9361712b1a63451b372f38663f424962-you-skipped-your-binary-o---", 0], ["000eea4e42beba5d3b34b6dd90a7e96e-it-s-just-so-easy-to-skip---", 0], ["e8c08e0524eec0d1b3d00f1661e7c45a-i-m-gonna-make-sure-my-ki---", 0], ["fa170d1ddab2122477108179debcfa12--you-ll-speak-rust-over-m---", 0], ["bd493035d847ac58c6ee0d80772d7bf9--i-bet-you--10-they-ll-gr---", 0], ["https://www.soundjay.com/misc/magic-chime-07.mp3", 1], ["f32cb1039b2eedd5932538ff1151d22e-anyways-let-s-look-